WEBVTT

00:06.484 --> 00:06.702
.

00:06.745 --> 00:09.009
- Previously, on "Shooter"...

00:10.227 --> 00:10.532
- You're having a heart attack,
Senator.

00:11.924 --> 00:12.577
- Who's Carlita Cruz,
Department of Agriculture?

00:13.839 --> 00:14.492
- Did you know you'd
set off such a shitstorm

00:14.536 --> 00:16.233
killing Senator Hayes?

00:16.277 --> 00:19.062
- Let's go somewhere
I know they can't track us.

00:19.106 --> 00:21.195
- That was Atlas issued.

00:21.238 --> 00:23.153
Access to the phone
is encrypted.

00:23.197 --> 00:25.503
- I haven't heard the name
Jimmy Poole in a long time.

00:25.547 --> 00:28.115
- He had a good job lined up
at the slaughterhouse.

00:28.158 --> 00:29.116
- Bama Cattle?

00:29.159 --> 00:30.595
- Red Bama?

00:30.639 --> 00:32.510
What business does
that backwoods drunk

00:32.554 --> 00:34.469
have with the Undersecretary
of Agriculture?

00:34.512 --> 00:36.862
- [gasps, grunts]

00:36.906 --> 00:39.343
- I was handling--
- You weren't handling shit.

00:39.387 --> 00:41.215
Swagger's not
some local loser

00:41.258 --> 00:43.869
you can push around;
he's a professional.

00:43.913 --> 00:45.784
- Atlas and this Swagger's

00:45.828 --> 00:48.091
been interlinked
since the beginning.

00:48.135 --> 00:49.614
- I wanted to be the first one
to officially

00:49.658 --> 00:50.789
welcome you to the family.

00:50.833 --> 00:52.487
- This family have a name?

00:52.530 --> 00:53.618
- Government said
the Phoenix Program

00:53.662 --> 00:55.098
ended after the war.

00:55.142 --> 00:56.534
What if they just
changed their name?

00:56.578 --> 00:59.102
- To Atlas?

00:59.146 --> 01:01.670
- If Phoenix became Atlas,

01:01.713 --> 01:04.368
then my dad was one
of the founding fathers.

01:05.587 --> 01:08.590
[phone ringing]

01:10.244 --> 01:12.594
- Isaac.

01:13.856 --> 01:15.553
[phone ringing]

01:15.597 --> 01:18.121
"Connect to download
target file."

01:29.306 --> 01:30.612
Adam Lee.

01:30.655 --> 01:33.267
- Open target for termination.

01:34.746 --> 01:36.270
Two D.C. locations?

01:36.313 --> 01:37.923
- They're using probabilities.

01:37.967 --> 01:40.839
Location one
has an 85% chance of contact.

01:40.883 --> 01:44.147
Location two only has 15%.

01:44.191 --> 01:46.584
So they gather data
on a target,

01:46.628 --> 01:48.456
then use an algorithm to--
[device beeps]

01:48.499 --> 01:49.761
What did you just do?

01:49.805 --> 01:51.198
- I signed up for
the first location.

01:51.241 --> 01:52.590
- But we don't even know
what target--

01:52.634 --> 01:53.591
- Someone else just grabbed
number two.

01:53.635 --> 01:55.158
- Shit.

01:55.202 --> 01:56.420
All right, I'll cover that.

01:56.464 --> 01:58.205
We're gonna have to split up.

01:58.248 --> 01:59.510
- What happens if the target
shows up in your sights

01:59.554 --> 02:01.599
instead of mine?
- Gee, I don't know, Dad.

02:01.643 --> 02:03.253
- If that happens, that means
you're gonna have to

02:03.297 --> 02:04.559
neutralize whatever operative
just signed up

02:04.602 --> 02:05.603
and take
the target on your own.

02:05.647 --> 02:07.866
- Well, then I'll handle it.

02:07.910 --> 02:09.259
Can't have it both ways, Isaac,

02:09.303 --> 02:10.391
choose a target
or the operative.

02:10.434 --> 02:11.479
- I want the target.

02:11.522 --> 02:14.482
[tense music]

02:14.525 --> 02:17.920
♪

02:17.963 --> 02:21.141
[grass crunching]

02:28.278 --> 02:31.542
- Awfully noisy
for a famous sniper.

02:31.586 --> 02:33.501
- If I was trying
to kill you,

02:33.544 --> 02:34.980
you wouldn't hear me.

02:35.024 --> 02:36.678
- Stand down, Frank.

02:36.721 --> 02:38.767
Never even get it
unholstered.

02:40.247 --> 02:42.423
You know, I've always liked
conversing out here

02:42.466 --> 02:45.382
in the fresh morning air
before the day's bullshit

02:45.426 --> 02:47.863
has gone and polluted it.

02:47.906 --> 02:50.387
- New target every day, huh?

02:50.431 --> 02:53.260
Today, pheasants.
Yesterday, Harris.

02:53.303 --> 02:54.652
Who's it gonna be tomorrow?

02:54.696 --> 02:57.525
- Ah, I don't know,
it's early yet.

02:57.568 --> 02:59.222
What the hell do you want?

02:59.266 --> 03:00.571
- I came to ask
what you want

03:00.615 --> 03:02.225
with an irrelevant
D.C. staffer.

03:02.269 --> 03:05.228
Or better yet,
what Atlas wants from him.

03:05.272 --> 03:07.970
- I thought you'd want answers
about your father.

03:08.013 --> 03:09.885
- Same thing.

03:11.626 --> 03:14.498
This proves my dad
was in Phoenix during Vietnam.

03:14.542 --> 03:18.372
We both know that Phoenix
became Atlas after that.

03:18.415 --> 03:20.417
- I'll be darned.

03:21.288 --> 03:23.507
You know, you seem to think

03:23.551 --> 03:27.032
that everything
is some big conspiracy

03:27.076 --> 03:30.819
when the truth
is much more biblical.

03:30.862 --> 03:32.386
- What's that supposed to mean?

03:32.429 --> 03:34.344
- It means
that when your daddy

03:34.388 --> 03:37.739
got back from Vietnam,
he was messed up good.

03:37.782 --> 03:39.567
So he found himself
some comfort

03:39.610 --> 03:42.526
in the arms of a pretty girl.

03:42.570 --> 03:44.746
His was called Edie Poole.

03:44.789 --> 03:46.313
- Jimmy Poole's wife?

03:46.356 --> 03:48.358
That's bullshit.
- You sure about that?

03:48.402 --> 03:50.491
- What I'm sure of
is there was a second shooter.

03:50.534 --> 03:53.494
- And he was a Poole too.

03:53.537 --> 03:55.583
Now you go on
with due diligence

03:55.626 --> 03:56.845
and you'll see that I'm right.

03:56.888 --> 04:00.022
Now, what is your interest
in this kid?

04:00.065 --> 04:03.765
You turn him over to me,
and I'll leave you be.

04:03.808 --> 04:05.027
- [grunts]

04:05.070 --> 04:06.550
[coughing]

04:06.594 --> 04:09.553
♪

04:09.597 --> 04:12.556
- Happy huntin'.

04:12.600 --> 04:15.559
[dramatic music]

04:15.603 --> 04:22.653
♪

04:24.960 --> 04:25.177
.

04:25.221 --> 04:26.657
- Did he say what he wants
from me?

04:27.136 --> 04:28.355
- Nope.

04:28.398 --> 04:30.531
He was too busy spouting off
lies about my dad.

04:30.574 --> 04:32.968
But he's not gonna stop
coming at you.

04:33.011 --> 04:34.143
And I'm sorry, man,
but I can't have

04:34.186 --> 04:35.318
that danger around my family.

04:35.362 --> 04:37.320
- Oh, I completely understand.

04:37.364 --> 04:40.497
Uh, Texas and I are actually
in the midst of a...

04:40.541 --> 04:42.456
very mutual breakup.

04:42.499 --> 04:44.284
Thank you for the clothes.

04:44.327 --> 04:46.024
I will mail them to you, uh...

04:46.068 --> 04:48.418
once I've washed the fear
out of them.

04:48.462 --> 04:50.333
- Keep 'em.
I already talked to Nadine.

04:50.377 --> 04:52.683
I'll take you to Dallas.
She's gonna fly in,

04:52.727 --> 04:54.424
make sure you get
someplace safe.

04:54.468 --> 04:56.252
- I can't decide if the fact
that my ex-girlfriend

04:56.296 --> 05:00.256
is now my babysitter
is kind of hot or kind of sad.

05:00.300 --> 05:02.476
- I'm gonna go check in with
my wife and then we'll roll.

05:02.519 --> 05:05.087
- Hey, Dallas is five hours
from here, right?

05:05.130 --> 05:06.262
- Yeah, that's why
we got to get moving.

05:06.306 --> 05:08.090
- Okay,
I'll--I'll take the bus.

05:08.133 --> 05:09.221
- Ah--ah,
that's not a good idea.

05:09.265 --> 05:10.571
- Swagger,
don't argue with me.

05:10.614 --> 05:14.183
I'm a grown man.
I can accept the--the risks.

05:14.226 --> 05:16.403
I will, however,
take you up on a ride

05:16.446 --> 05:17.708
to the nearest bus station.

05:17.752 --> 05:21.538
Also, I was thinking,
maybe a gun?

05:21.582 --> 05:24.062
- [scoffs]

05:24.106 --> 05:26.108
So he shoots one guy's face off

05:26.151 --> 05:28.197
and all of a sudden,
he wants a gun.

05:28.240 --> 05:30.199
- Let's just say
my position on guns

05:30.242 --> 05:33.115
has changed dramatically
in the last 24 hours.

05:33.158 --> 05:34.508
- Try this instead.

05:36.379 --> 05:38.338
- It's very pink.
- It's pepper spray.

05:38.381 --> 05:40.209
Julie used to carry it
up in Seattle.

05:40.252 --> 05:43.081
Suits you.
- Thanks for that.

05:43.125 --> 05:44.996
- Okay, seriously...

05:45.040 --> 05:46.563
if you get into any trouble,

05:46.607 --> 05:48.435
just go for
the vulnerable areas, okay?

05:48.478 --> 05:51.394
Your groin, eyes, knee.
- Yeah, yeah.

05:51.438 --> 05:54.397
Groin, eyes, knee.
Thank you.

05:54.441 --> 05:57.400
[tense music]

05:57.444 --> 06:04.451
♪

06:07.671 --> 06:10.761
[line ringing]

06:11.806 --> 06:14.461
- Hey.
I've got eyes on location one.

06:14.504 --> 06:16.463
- Location two in position.

06:16.506 --> 06:18.290
- Good, we have some time.

06:18.334 --> 06:20.249
- Not really.
I'm wheels up to Dallas

06:20.292 --> 06:21.685
to pick up Harris soon.

06:21.729 --> 06:23.339
- Just can't get
rid of that guy, huh?

06:23.383 --> 06:24.819
- Bob Lee says
he knows something.

06:24.862 --> 06:26.473
Maybe he'll prove useful.

06:26.516 --> 06:28.344
- Like a screen door
in a submarine?

06:28.388 --> 06:30.346
- [scoffs]
What would you have me do?

06:30.390 --> 06:32.043
Leave him
to fend off Atlas alone?

06:32.087 --> 06:34.176
- I'm not in the business
of saving lives, Nadine.

06:34.219 --> 06:35.612
I leave that to you
and Swagger.

06:35.656 --> 06:37.745
- Except right now,
we are saving a life.

06:37.788 --> 06:39.442
We take the target alive

06:39.486 --> 06:40.835
so we can find out
what he knows,

06:40.878 --> 06:42.445
That's how this
whole thing works, right?

06:42.489 --> 06:45.274
[gun cocks]
- Copy that.

06:45.317 --> 06:47.145
[both giggling,
indistinct chatter]

06:47.189 --> 06:50.192
- Hey, ladies.
- We're making cookies, Daddy.

06:50.235 --> 06:52.063
- I can see that, Mouse.

06:52.107 --> 06:54.152
- Auntie Ann's teaching us
how to make 'em from scratch.

06:54.196 --> 06:55.458
- Yeah?
- And I don't share

06:55.502 --> 06:58.243
my top secret recipe
with just anyone.

06:58.287 --> 06:59.810
- Do you want to help us?

06:59.854 --> 07:02.378
- Oh, I wish I could but
Daddy's got to run an errand.

07:02.422 --> 07:04.424
But could you save me
a couple for later?

07:04.467 --> 07:07.470
- For a midnight snack?
[both laugh]

07:07.514 --> 07:10.168
- Yes, Mouse,
for a midnight snack.

07:10.212 --> 07:12.693
Babe, you got a minute?
- Yeah.

07:16.697 --> 07:18.655
Did you even come to bed
last night?

07:18.699 --> 07:20.483
- Briefly.

07:20.527 --> 07:23.355
Couldn't sleep again.

07:23.399 --> 07:26.097
- So, um, this errand,

07:26.141 --> 07:27.403
does it have anything to do

07:27.447 --> 07:30.232
with your friend
in the panic room?

07:30.275 --> 07:32.626
- Yeah, that's just
Nadine's ex, Harris Downey.

07:32.669 --> 07:34.410
She asked if he could crash
here for a couple of days,

07:34.454 --> 07:36.499
but I'm taking him
to the bus station now,

07:36.543 --> 07:37.718
then I'll be home.

07:37.761 --> 07:39.589
- Look,
whatever trouble he's in

07:39.633 --> 07:42.462
I'm guessing it has to do with
your father's death, right?

07:43.767 --> 07:46.466
- You saw the bullets, Jules.
There was a second shooter.

07:46.509 --> 07:48.685
- But I also heard Sam,

07:48.729 --> 07:50.295
and he said that it was
probably a Poole,

07:50.339 --> 07:52.689
so case closed.

07:52.733 --> 07:54.648
- Sam said what?

07:56.563 --> 07:58.434
Yo, Sam!
[knocks on door]

08:00.697 --> 08:02.917
- You here to raise hell
about me giving Julie a job?

08:02.960 --> 08:06.181
Or just to take an old man
to lunch?

08:06.224 --> 08:07.878
- That all depends
on how you answer my questions.

08:07.922 --> 08:10.533
- Oh, Lord.

08:10.577 --> 08:13.275
Here we go.

08:13.318 --> 08:14.798
Shoot.

08:14.842 --> 08:16.844
- The other day you said
if somebody else shot my dad

08:16.887 --> 08:18.410
it would probably been
another Poole.

08:18.454 --> 08:21.283
What did that mean?

08:21.326 --> 08:24.591
- Those Pooles
are like cockroaches, son.

08:24.634 --> 08:26.375
You tell yourself there's
just the one in front of you

08:26.418 --> 08:28.464
and there's always more.

08:28.508 --> 08:30.510
- I heard a rumor.
I need to know

08:30.553 --> 08:32.816
if that's all it is.

08:32.860 --> 08:35.210
Edie Poole, my father.

08:36.516 --> 08:38.735
- That's it.

08:38.779 --> 08:41.303
I already let you sully
his corpse.

08:41.346 --> 08:43.479
I won't let you do the same
to his reputation.

08:43.523 --> 08:44.959
- That's not a no.

08:45.002 --> 08:47.831
- You listen to me, Bob Lee.

08:47.875 --> 08:50.530
Earl loved June.

08:50.573 --> 08:53.184
Through and through.

08:53.228 --> 08:55.186
- I just want the truth.

08:55.230 --> 08:56.536
I deserve that much.

08:58.320 --> 09:00.235
- It's not my secret to tell.

09:00.278 --> 09:02.367
- All right, well, then tell me
where Edie is. I'll ask her.

09:02.411 --> 09:05.545
- I haven't the faintest idea
where that woman is.

09:05.588 --> 09:07.808
- I'ma find her myself.

09:07.851 --> 09:10.245
- Wait just a damn second.
Bob Lee!

09:16.860 --> 09:18.645
[phone ringing]
- It's taking too long.

09:18.688 --> 09:20.211
Lee should be here by now.

09:20.255 --> 09:21.517
- Yeah, I know...

09:21.561 --> 09:22.518
[tense music]

09:22.562 --> 09:24.389
Shit, he's here.

09:24.433 --> 09:25.913
- Damn it.
All right,

09:25.956 --> 09:27.523
there'll be at least
one Atlas operative,

09:27.567 --> 09:29.220
maybe two.

09:29.264 --> 09:30.613
- Yeah, I know.

09:30.657 --> 09:31.614
- Remember,
it could be anyone.

09:31.658 --> 09:32.963
- Yeah, I know that too.

09:33.007 --> 09:35.226
- What do you see?
Who do you see?

09:35.270 --> 09:37.664
- Isaac, shut up.

09:37.707 --> 09:39.491
♪

09:39.535 --> 09:41.493
- Memphis?

09:41.537 --> 09:42.494
Shit.

09:42.538 --> 09:49.589
♪

09:51.808 --> 09:53.593
- Hey! Hey!

09:53.636 --> 09:55.725
- [grunting]

09:55.769 --> 09:57.684
- What the hell?

09:57.727 --> 10:02.036
♪

10:02.079 --> 10:03.037
[gunshot]

10:03.080 --> 10:04.604
[screaming]

10:04.647 --> 10:07.737
- It's Atlas.
Come on, let's go.

10:34.764 --> 10:36.374
[knocking at door]

10:40.944 --> 10:42.816
[banging on door]

10:44.731 --> 10:45.993
- Hey!

10:46.036 --> 10:47.429
Thought I told you last time,

10:47.472 --> 10:48.735
Swagger,
you ain't welcome here.

10:48.778 --> 10:51.781
- I ain't here for no trouble,
Johnny.

10:51.825 --> 10:53.740
- Then what the hell
you doing trespassing?

10:53.783 --> 10:55.524
- I don't give a shit
about what you got

10:55.567 --> 10:57.613
going on down there.
I'm still looking for Edie.

10:57.657 --> 10:59.702
Now, is your grandma
or--or you daughter--

10:59.746 --> 11:00.703
[electricity crackling]

11:00.747 --> 11:03.750
[dark music]

11:07.362 --> 11:07.579
.

11:07.623 --> 11:10.452
[hollow ringing tones]

11:20.810 --> 11:23.944
- Bet you woke up now.

11:23.987 --> 11:25.423
- You don't want to do that.

11:25.467 --> 11:26.947
- No?
Why's that?

11:26.990 --> 11:29.732
- 'Cause I'm not gonna
be locked up here forever.

11:29.776 --> 11:31.603
- True.
After you're dead,

11:31.647 --> 11:34.432
we'll untie you
so we can keep that chair.

11:37.435 --> 11:40.569
Who'd you tell
about our operation, Swagger?

11:40.612 --> 11:42.049
Who knows you're here?

11:42.092 --> 11:43.485
- Nobody, man.
I told you.

11:43.528 --> 11:44.878
I'm here about Edie.

11:44.921 --> 11:51.623
♪

11:52.624 --> 11:54.017
- What the hell's wrong
with you, Dad?

11:54.061 --> 11:55.584
Help me get him up.

11:55.627 --> 11:56.977
- You ain't supposed
to be here, Susie.

11:57.020 --> 11:59.370
Mind your own business.

11:59.414 --> 12:02.286
♪

12:02.330 --> 12:04.636
- Hey!

12:04.680 --> 12:06.029
- [grunts]

12:06.073 --> 12:08.858
- Get the hell out of here,
both of you.

12:08.902 --> 12:15.865
♪

12:15.909 --> 12:18.476
- Don't you think
it's a little cliché,

12:18.520 --> 12:20.914
dealing drugs,
beating up young girls?

12:20.957 --> 12:23.655
You know, it's guys like you
that make some people

12:23.699 --> 12:25.527
not think too kindly
of the South.

12:25.570 --> 12:26.789
♪

12:26.833 --> 12:28.748
[gun clicks]

12:28.791 --> 12:30.488
♪

12:30.532 --> 12:32.795
- The objective was
to neutralize the Atlas threat

12:32.839 --> 12:34.536
and bring the target here,
which I did.

12:34.579 --> 12:35.711
- You didn't
neutralize a threat.

12:35.755 --> 12:36.973
You shot it in the shoulder.

12:37.017 --> 12:38.845
Now the SatPhone is burnt
and Atlas knows

12:38.888 --> 12:40.977
we're on to them.

12:41.021 --> 12:43.458
- Wh--I need to go
get Harris.

12:43.501 --> 12:44.894
- So go.

12:49.725 --> 12:52.902
Here.
Calm your nerves.

12:57.994 --> 13:00.823
- Okay, so are you guys

13:00.867 --> 13:02.782
gonna tell me
who you are now?

13:02.825 --> 13:05.915
'Cause you're not Atlas
and you're not cops.

13:05.959 --> 13:07.525
So who are you?

13:07.569 --> 13:08.875
- We're the people
that saved your life.

13:08.918 --> 13:10.702
- And we suggest
you start paying that debt

13:10.746 --> 13:13.053
by telling us why they want you
dead to begin with.

13:19.059 --> 13:21.583
He tells me
what I want to know,

13:21.626 --> 13:22.671
he'll be fine.

13:22.714 --> 13:25.456
[eerie tones]

13:25.500 --> 13:27.850
[door opens, closes]

13:27.894 --> 13:29.025
- Is she coming back?

13:29.069 --> 13:31.941
♪

13:31.985 --> 13:34.030
- I need to know
who you told about us.

13:34.074 --> 13:35.684
- Did it ever occur to you
that I didn't know shit

13:35.727 --> 13:37.599
about your backwoods
coke operation

13:37.642 --> 13:39.557
till you decided to tie me up
in the middle of it?

13:39.601 --> 13:42.125
- Coke?
Please.

13:42.169 --> 13:44.084
America wants opioids now.

13:44.127 --> 13:45.737
That shit sells itself.

13:45.781 --> 13:47.609
- Hey, man, you want that
on your conscience,

13:47.652 --> 13:49.524
ain't no business of mine.

13:49.567 --> 13:51.613
I came here with questions
about Edie.

13:51.656 --> 13:53.963
You answer 'em,
I was never here.

13:54.007 --> 13:56.096
- And if I don't?

13:56.139 --> 13:59.577
- Well, I imagine the sheriff
is a lot less forgiving

13:59.621 --> 14:00.883
when it comes to drug dealers.

14:00.927 --> 14:02.754
- [chuckles]

14:02.798 --> 14:05.845
Oh, you got some big ones,
Swagger.

14:05.888 --> 14:07.542
I'll give you that.

14:07.585 --> 14:10.023
Giving me orders
when you don't got shit.

14:10.066 --> 14:11.459
[grunts]

14:11.502 --> 14:13.940
[gagging]

14:13.983 --> 14:15.550
- Make a sound
and I'll shoot you.

14:15.593 --> 14:18.466
You answer my questions,
I was never here.

14:18.509 --> 14:19.859
- So ask, asshole.

14:19.902 --> 14:20.990
- Was there another Poole
on a long gun

14:21.034 --> 14:22.513
the night my father was killed?

14:22.557 --> 14:24.907
- What the hell
you talking about?

14:24.951 --> 14:26.953
- I'm about to break your arm
at the elbow.

14:26.996 --> 14:28.911
That's six months
of no jerking off, we clear?

14:28.955 --> 14:30.826
- If we know Uncle Jimmy
was gonna meet your daddy

14:30.870 --> 14:32.784
that night,
there'd have been 20 of us

14:32.828 --> 14:34.569
in that field, not one.

14:34.612 --> 14:36.005
Trust me, no Poole would have
killed your daddy

14:36.049 --> 14:38.921
and kept his mouth shut
about it.

14:38.965 --> 14:40.923
- Anybody ever run their mouth
about Edie and my dad?

14:40.967 --> 14:43.012
- Even she wouldn't
have stooped so low.

14:43.056 --> 14:44.796
- I need to find her!

14:44.840 --> 14:48.931
- Good luck, I ain't seen
that bitch in 30 years.

14:48.975 --> 14:51.803
- Don't.
Back in there.

14:55.111 --> 14:56.765
All right.

14:56.808 --> 14:58.158
I'm gonna get up now

14:58.201 --> 15:01.683
and then you are too, slow.

15:01.726 --> 15:03.554
Come on now.

15:03.598 --> 15:06.079
- [grunting]

15:09.996 --> 15:11.780
- I'm gonna be keeping this

15:11.823 --> 15:13.129
and you're gonna be keeping
your hands to yourself

15:13.173 --> 15:15.088
from now on, you understand me?

15:15.131 --> 15:16.959
- Get off my property,
asshole.

15:17.003 --> 15:18.874
- Oh, gladly.

15:18.918 --> 15:21.833
Get in that room.
Go on.

15:27.187 --> 15:29.711
- You shouldn't have
helped him, you stupid bitch.

15:29.754 --> 15:32.714
[clattering]

15:32.757 --> 15:35.717
[dark music]

15:35.760 --> 15:42.202
♪

15:42.245 --> 15:43.507
- Hey!

15:43.551 --> 15:45.553
♪

15:45.596 --> 15:47.729
- [grunting]

15:47.772 --> 15:50.993
- [gasps]
- [grunts]

15:51.037 --> 15:53.039
- Come on, I'll take you
someplace safe,

15:53.082 --> 15:54.866
maybe your mom's.
- She's gone.

15:54.910 --> 15:55.998
- Well, I can't leave you here.

15:56.042 --> 15:57.304
- This is where I live.

15:57.347 --> 15:59.697
- It doesn't have to be.

16:03.179 --> 16:05.660
- Don't hurt him!

16:05.703 --> 16:08.010
- You take better care of her,
you understand?

16:08.054 --> 16:09.925
And tell your brother
I'll be checking in.

16:09.969 --> 16:11.535
Anybody around here
hurts her again,

16:11.579 --> 16:13.668
I'm coming back,
but it's gonna end different.

16:13.711 --> 16:14.974
- [choking]
Okay.

16:28.770 --> 16:31.207
[tense music]

16:31.251 --> 16:38.301
♪

16:47.223 --> 16:49.051
- Why do you always
drive to this feed store

16:49.095 --> 16:52.054
when there are places
closer to home?

16:52.098 --> 16:56.232
- [sighs] There's a girl
that works here.

16:56.276 --> 16:58.887
Her husband got himself
in trouble a while back.

16:58.930 --> 17:00.149
I had to put him away.

17:00.193 --> 17:01.759
- Mm.

17:01.803 --> 17:04.849
- So I check in on her
from time to time.

17:04.893 --> 17:08.070
- You're a good man,
Earl Swagger.

17:08.114 --> 17:10.072
That's what Ma would say.

17:15.295 --> 17:17.819
- Oh,

17:17.862 --> 17:19.864
morning, Sheriff.

17:19.908 --> 17:21.214
This must be your boy.

17:21.257 --> 17:22.302
- Hi.

17:25.609 --> 17:26.871
- Hello, I'm--

17:26.915 --> 17:30.179
- Is my order
all ready then?

17:30.223 --> 17:32.007
- Course,
got it inside for you.

17:32.051 --> 17:33.965
- I'll be right in.

17:40.146 --> 17:43.018
- That's her?
She's nice.

17:45.325 --> 17:47.240
- This world is shit,
Bob Lee.

17:47.283 --> 17:48.850
- Yes, sir.

17:48.893 --> 17:50.112
- Don't just say "Yes, sir."

17:50.156 --> 17:51.853
Think about what
I'm saying to you.

17:51.896 --> 17:53.985
[solemn music]

17:54.029 --> 17:55.770
- Yes, sir.

17:55.813 --> 17:59.295
- That's why a real man
commits himself to service.

17:59.339 --> 18:00.949
To remember
that there are things

18:00.992 --> 18:04.170
that are more important
than our own selfishness.

18:04.213 --> 18:08.957
♪

18:09.000 --> 18:11.090
Wait here.

18:11.133 --> 18:18.140
♪

18:19.185 --> 18:20.186
- Are you here?

18:20.229 --> 18:21.709
Nadine, the guy next to me

18:21.752 --> 18:24.059
was literally
eating Chinese food

18:24.103 --> 18:26.148
while trimming his nose hairs.

18:26.192 --> 18:27.367
I need to get back
to civilization.

18:27.410 --> 18:29.108
I don't see you.
Where are you?

18:29.151 --> 18:31.022
- I just got here.
I'll be down in 60 seconds.

18:31.066 --> 18:32.807
Stay put.
- Oh, great,

18:32.850 --> 18:35.157
because I'm sure no one
can kill me in 60 seconds.

18:35.201 --> 18:36.898
- No one's here to kill you,
Harris.

18:36.941 --> 18:38.029
If they knew
you were on that bus,

18:38.073 --> 18:39.161
they would have done it then

18:39.205 --> 18:40.423
when you were a sitting duck.

18:40.467 --> 18:44.471
- Oh--oh, Jesus.
Uh, okay.

18:44.514 --> 18:47.343
- Just stay calm, act like you
have somewhere to be.

18:47.387 --> 18:49.128
- I do have somewhere to be,
my old life,

18:49.171 --> 18:50.999
where reading
a presidential tweet

18:51.042 --> 18:54.045
was about the most excitement
I'd have in a day.

18:55.221 --> 18:57.136
I-I feel like everybody's
watching me.

18:57.179 --> 18:58.876
All right, hold on a second,
I'm gonna try something.

18:58.920 --> 19:00.400
- No, Harris,
don't try anything.

19:00.443 --> 19:03.229
Just stay where you are.

19:03.272 --> 19:05.318
Harris.

19:05.361 --> 19:06.928
Harris?

19:08.843 --> 19:11.498
-Okay, right, I lost 'em.
Never mind, false alarm.

19:11.541 --> 19:13.195
- Take it down a notch, Harris.

19:13.239 --> 19:14.892
- I'm sorry, I'm sorry,
all the excitement,

19:14.936 --> 19:16.459
I get a little--
- Hey, man, you got a dollar?

19:16.503 --> 19:18.331
- Jesus!
- [screaming]

19:18.374 --> 19:20.028
- Harris?
- Come with me, sir.

19:20.071 --> 19:22.117
- Hey, somebody call the cops!
- Harris! Harris!

19:22.161 --> 19:25.033
[people screaming]

19:25.076 --> 19:26.208
Harris!

19:26.252 --> 19:29.211
[exciting music]

19:29.255 --> 19:36.305
♪

19:46.837 --> 19:47.229
.

19:47.273 --> 19:49.579
- Hey, home in time for lunch,
huh?

19:52.365 --> 19:53.453
- [sighs]

19:53.496 --> 19:55.411
What's wrong?

19:59.894 --> 20:02.244
- My father w--

20:02.288 --> 20:05.247
was having an affair
with Jimmy Poole's wife.

20:05.291 --> 20:06.857
- What?

20:08.772 --> 20:10.252
Are you sure?

20:10.296 --> 20:11.688
- Yeah, I'm sure.

20:11.732 --> 20:14.169
I even remember once
he took me to the feed store

20:14.213 --> 20:17.477
where she worked--
apparently still does.

20:18.782 --> 20:20.567
- So are you gonna
go talk to her?

20:20.610 --> 20:22.438
- For what? Baby, the more
I learn about him,

20:22.482 --> 20:25.224
the more I realize everything
I knew about him was a lie.

20:25.267 --> 20:26.790
- Look, that's not true,
okay.

20:26.834 --> 20:29.663
I just--I think that--
[phone ringing]

20:32.318 --> 20:34.711
- It's Nadine.

20:34.755 --> 20:36.278
[phone beeps]

20:36.322 --> 20:37.366
Yeah?

20:37.410 --> 20:38.802
- Hey, Harris is gone.

20:38.846 --> 20:40.717
Freaked out,
got himself grabbed up.

20:40.761 --> 20:42.763
I've combed the place
top to bottom.

20:42.806 --> 20:44.373
I've got nothing.
- Damn it.

20:44.417 --> 20:46.288
I knew I shouldn't
have let him go alone.

20:46.332 --> 20:47.855
It's got to be Red.

20:47.898 --> 20:49.422
- I know.

20:49.465 --> 20:50.814
Do you have any idea
where'd he take him?

20:50.858 --> 20:52.294
- Out of Texas,

20:52.338 --> 20:54.296
Probably on a plane by now.

20:54.340 --> 20:55.776
- Isaac's got an arms broker
in custody.

20:55.819 --> 20:57.299
He's worked for Atlas.
I'll lean in on him.

20:57.343 --> 20:58.431
He might be able to lead us

20:58.474 --> 21:00.433
to active Atlas locations.

21:00.476 --> 21:02.217
- Yeah, have him check
anywhere he sent anything

21:02.261 --> 21:03.653
the last few weeks.

21:03.697 --> 21:06.613
My gut tells me that Red
will stay local, rural.

21:06.656 --> 21:08.310
He's not gonna
take Harris to D.C.,

21:08.354 --> 21:10.443
not if somebody else
wants what he might have.

21:10.486 --> 21:12.183
Text me if you get a lead.

21:13.837 --> 21:15.796
I'll meet you when I can.

21:17.406 --> 21:18.886
Harris got grabbed.

21:18.929 --> 21:21.454
- What does that
have to do with you?

21:21.497 --> 21:24.892
- Come on, Jule.
- [sighs] I'm serious.

21:24.935 --> 21:27.416
If it's not one conspiracy,
it's another.

21:27.460 --> 21:28.852
- Yeah, but this
isn't a conspiracy.

21:28.896 --> 21:31.333
This is me trying to help
save someone's life.

21:31.377 --> 21:32.508
You don't really want me
to just walk away

21:32.552 --> 21:34.293
from that, do you?

21:35.555 --> 21:37.687
- Do what you got to do.

21:42.692 --> 21:44.520
[sighs]

21:47.871 --> 21:49.482
- I asked you a question.

21:49.525 --> 21:52.659
- [sighs] I'm just a broker.

21:52.702 --> 21:53.921
A middleman.

21:53.964 --> 21:55.488
- What's your expertise?

21:55.531 --> 21:57.490
- I sell all kinds of shit.
Okay?

21:57.533 --> 21:59.492
Guns, tanks, meds,
whatever you need.

21:59.535 --> 22:01.842
- What does Atlas need?

22:01.885 --> 22:03.365
- Explosives.

22:03.409 --> 22:04.366
[phone rings]

22:04.410 --> 22:06.847
[line ringing]

22:06.890 --> 22:08.501
- I'm still with our friend,
Memphis.

22:08.544 --> 22:10.503
What's the sit-rep?
- Atlas got Harris.

22:10.546 --> 22:13.680
We need to pressure Lee
on likely holding locations.

22:13.723 --> 22:15.290
Turn the heat up
but keep him breathing.

22:15.334 --> 22:17.248
- Copy that, Memphis.

22:18.772 --> 22:20.643
- I need to piss.

22:20.687 --> 22:21.731
Hey!
- Not until you tell me

22:21.775 --> 22:23.385
where you sent the explosives.

22:23.429 --> 22:24.778
- What the hell, man?
- I want exact locations.

22:24.821 --> 22:27.911
- Stop it!
- You like to party, right?

22:27.955 --> 22:29.957
That's what I read
in your Atlas file.

22:30.000 --> 22:32.046
This'll just look like
a drunken night gone wrong.

22:32.089 --> 22:33.569
- What, you are Atlas?

22:33.613 --> 22:35.005
- I am who I need to be
minute by minute.

22:35.049 --> 22:36.659
- All right, man--
man, I-I've sent stuff

22:36.703 --> 22:38.487
all over the world, all right?
Iran, Kuwait.

22:38.531 --> 22:40.489
Last month it was
some small city in Nigeria

22:40.533 --> 22:41.969
called Yolo.

22:42.012 --> 22:43.884
- Where that bomb killed
30 kids in school?

22:43.927 --> 22:45.625
- I told you, I'm a middleman.

22:45.668 --> 22:47.061
If I didn't set up the sales,
someone else would.

22:47.104 --> 22:48.802
Come on, man, hate the game,
not the player--

22:48.845 --> 22:51.326
[shouts, screams]

22:51.370 --> 22:52.545
Oh! Okay!

22:52.588 --> 22:54.416
Let me back in!
Let me back in!

22:54.460 --> 22:56.549
- Want domestic locations,
recent.

22:56.592 --> 22:58.028
Virginia?
Texas?

22:58.072 --> 22:59.987
- Domestic shipments
have all been Semtex.

23:00.030 --> 23:02.903
Uh, last shipment was
to a-an airfield in Missouri/

23:02.946 --> 23:05.427
It's called Five Mile!
It's called Five Mile!

23:05.471 --> 23:06.733
- Five Mile?

23:06.776 --> 23:08.561
- It's called Five--
Jesus.

23:08.604 --> 23:09.736
[screams]

23:09.779 --> 23:11.433
[thud]

23:11.477 --> 23:12.913
[panicked screams]

23:12.956 --> 23:15.916
[tense music]

23:15.959 --> 23:23.010
♪

23:28.494 --> 23:31.932
- Mr. Downey, come in, come i--

23:31.975 --> 23:33.760
Take those cuffs off.

23:33.803 --> 23:37.328
I told you this would not
be necessary.

23:45.598 --> 23:47.382
That's all.

23:49.950 --> 23:52.387
I am sorry about that.

23:52.431 --> 23:55.346
Please, have a seat.

24:05.095 --> 24:06.793
Here.

24:10.536 --> 24:13.539
I knew you were a bright one.

24:15.758 --> 24:17.020
Mm.

24:24.071 --> 24:26.160
First of all,
let me apologize

24:26.203 --> 24:29.119
for going through such measures
to get you alone.

24:29.163 --> 24:31.774
Disruptive but necessary.

24:31.818 --> 24:34.385
- That's subjective.

24:34.429 --> 24:36.649
- Yes, well,
we won't have to worry

24:36.692 --> 24:39.869
about any interruptions here.

24:39.913 --> 24:41.392
- What do you want from me?

24:41.436 --> 24:44.570
- I want to offer you a job,
for one.

24:44.613 --> 24:46.528
You worked for Hayes.

24:46.572 --> 24:50.445
You know how our behemoth
of a government operates.

24:50.489 --> 24:52.534
- Thought I did,
until recently.

24:52.578 --> 24:55.755
- Well, all this fighting,
hiding, sneaking around,

24:55.798 --> 24:57.844
that's not you, Harris.
You're a city kid.

24:57.887 --> 25:01.021
You drink lattes.
You read "The New Yorker."

25:01.064 --> 25:03.023
And if you come
to work for me,

25:03.066 --> 25:05.155
you can have
your old life back.

25:07.636 --> 25:12.554
Your former boss was holding
onto something of mine.

25:12.598 --> 25:16.427
It's time I got it back.

25:16.471 --> 25:17.428
- What is it?

25:17.472 --> 25:18.995
- A decryption device,

25:19.039 --> 25:20.562
one of a kind.

25:20.606 --> 25:22.825
Made by
a very smart mathematician,

25:22.869 --> 25:24.566
Hoffman, a German,

25:24.610 --> 25:27.090
but we can forgive him
for that.

25:27.134 --> 25:29.049
- What's it decrypt?

25:29.092 --> 25:30.572
- That's classified,

25:30.616 --> 25:32.966
but internally
we call it the God Box.

25:33.009 --> 25:34.533
Now I am told
that you're the one

25:34.576 --> 25:36.665
who emptied his safe.
Is that true?

25:36.709 --> 25:38.667
- Yes.

25:38.711 --> 25:40.451
This was not in there.

25:42.715 --> 25:45.718
- Have you ever head the saying
"Man is not what he is,

25:45.761 --> 25:47.850
he is what he hides"?

25:47.894 --> 25:49.591
[tense music]

25:49.635 --> 25:51.158
- Telling you the truth.

25:51.201 --> 25:54.204
I-I've never seen anything
like that in my life.

25:54.248 --> 25:55.815
♪

25:55.858 --> 25:58.034
- That's fine, Harris.
That's--that's fine.

25:58.078 --> 26:02.125
♪

26:08.131 --> 26:12.005
- Hi, I'm--I'm looking
for Edie Poole.

26:12.048 --> 26:14.268
- Do I know you?

26:14.311 --> 26:15.791
- I'm Julie Swagger.

26:19.665 --> 26:22.058
- Let's get some fresh air.

26:22.102 --> 26:23.930
- I'm sorry for
just showing up like this.

26:23.973 --> 26:26.280
I--look, I-I'm here
for my husband.

26:26.323 --> 26:28.543
He's, you know, been searching
for answers about Earl

26:28.587 --> 26:31.067
and I--
- I-It's all true, dear.

26:31.111 --> 26:33.635
I promised myself years ago
that if Earl's boy

26:33.679 --> 26:36.159
ever sought me out,
I would tell him the truth.

26:37.987 --> 26:42.252
- [sighs]
How--how did it all start?

26:42.296 --> 26:44.254
- The church assigned
all of us young girls

26:44.298 --> 26:48.563
a local soldier to write to
during Vietnam.

26:48.607 --> 26:50.957
I got Earl.

26:51.000 --> 26:54.700
Course, it was friendly then,
innocent.

26:54.743 --> 26:56.745
It wasn't until Earl
arrested Jimmy

26:56.789 --> 27:00.053
more than a decade later
that it became more.

27:00.096 --> 27:02.621
- That's why Jimmy killed Earl.
Because he found out?

27:02.664 --> 27:04.144
- No.
No one knew.

27:04.187 --> 27:05.798
- Oh, come on, Edie.
It's West Texas.

27:05.841 --> 27:07.669
Gossip spreads faster
than wildfire.

27:07.713 --> 27:10.890
- If Jimmy knew
then all the Pooles knew.

27:10.933 --> 27:12.108
And if that was the case
I'd have been

27:12.152 --> 27:14.023
six-feet under
the very next day.

27:14.067 --> 27:16.852
In a town that small, sometimes
the only privacy you get

27:16.896 --> 27:18.680
is keeping a secret.

27:18.724 --> 27:21.161
You know, Earl wasn't much one
for the limelight.

27:21.204 --> 27:23.859
But he loved the job.

27:23.903 --> 27:25.861
Gave him purpose.

27:27.036 --> 27:29.691
- Yeah, I think, uh--

27:29.735 --> 27:31.911
I think Bob Lee misses it too.

27:31.954 --> 27:35.131
You know,
the purpose of a mission.

27:35.175 --> 27:38.700
You know, he's back,
it's just not the same.

27:40.049 --> 27:41.616
- Can you wait here a minute?

27:41.660 --> 27:43.836
I got something for you.
- All right.

27:43.879 --> 27:45.838
- Something that might
help Bob Lee understand

27:45.881 --> 27:47.840
the man his daddy was.

27:47.883 --> 27:50.320
[country music over radio]
- ♪ It's cold outside

27:50.364 --> 27:52.235
♪ I just wanna stay in bed

27:52.279 --> 27:55.238
[music continues faintly]

27:55.282 --> 28:02.332
♪

28:06.902 --> 28:09.688
- You just getting here?
- Yep.

28:11.385 --> 28:13.735
- Memphis could have
got you a plane.

28:13.779 --> 28:14.997
- Nah, the drive did me good.

28:15.041 --> 28:16.390
I needed time to think.

28:16.433 --> 28:21.003
♪

28:21.047 --> 28:22.135
- Finally.

28:22.178 --> 28:23.614
- Had to wait for light anyway.

28:23.658 --> 28:26.008
- I know.

28:26.052 --> 28:27.880
I just hope he's okay.

28:27.923 --> 28:29.272
- I wouldn't worry too much.

28:29.316 --> 28:31.144
After spending two days
with him,

28:31.187 --> 28:33.755
I'm pretty sure Harris can
run his mouth until a rescue.

28:33.799 --> 28:36.105
- All right.

28:36.149 --> 28:37.672
Locations.

28:37.716 --> 28:39.195
There's an old mining camp.

28:39.239 --> 28:41.371
It's been inactive for decades,
land abandoned,

28:41.415 --> 28:43.896
but it was bought at auction
a few years ago.

28:43.939 --> 28:45.767
- I traced the sale.
Cash came from

28:45.811 --> 28:47.421
a government grant
for rural development,

28:47.464 --> 28:48.770
courtesy of
the Department of Ag.

28:48.814 --> 28:50.772
- That's Red.

28:50.816 --> 28:52.382
And you got all this intel
from the arms broker?

28:52.426 --> 28:54.776
- He sent Semtex
to the closest airfield

28:54.820 --> 28:57.387
a few weeks ago--
place called Five Mile.

28:57.431 --> 28:59.912
Two clicks over
the Missouri border.

28:59.955 --> 29:02.175
I connected the rest
of the dots to lead us here.

29:02.218 --> 29:04.786
So at first light,
I'll go in on foot.

29:04.830 --> 29:05.918
You take overwatch.

29:05.961 --> 29:07.397
Memphis,
keep the engine running.

29:07.441 --> 29:11.097
I'll grab Harris,
you'll be exfil.

29:11.140 --> 29:13.403
- How?
- How we gonna get out?

29:13.447 --> 29:15.928
- No, how did you connect
an airfield in Missouri

29:15.971 --> 29:17.407
to a mine in Oklahoma?

29:17.451 --> 29:20.019
How did you know
to tell her to trace the sale?

29:20.062 --> 29:21.324
- I've done this
once or twice.

29:21.368 --> 29:23.326
- You know I'm not about
to get played.

29:23.370 --> 29:26.329
[tense music]

29:26.373 --> 29:30.333
♪

29:30.377 --> 29:32.814
- I've been there before.

29:32.858 --> 29:35.121
For a meeting,
with Meachum.

29:35.164 --> 29:36.992
He had me flown
into Five Mile.

29:37.036 --> 29:39.299
And then they black-bagged me
across the Oklahoma border

29:39.342 --> 29:40.953
to the mine.

29:40.996 --> 29:44.173
That's where we decided
it would be you.

29:44.217 --> 29:49.700
♪

29:49.744 --> 29:52.225
- You're on overwatch.
I'm going in on foot.

29:52.268 --> 29:55.315
Do not fire a single shot
until you know Harris is safe.

29:55.358 --> 29:57.012
- Bob Lee.

29:57.056 --> 30:00.320
♪

30:00.363 --> 30:02.278
- See you at dawn.

30:02.322 --> 30:07.153
♪

30:09.503 --> 30:09.720
.

30:09.764 --> 30:12.506
[tense music]

30:13.072 --> 30:19.600
♪

30:22.385 --> 30:24.605
- I count six so far,
two vehicles.

30:24.648 --> 30:25.824
- Bob Lee?

30:25.867 --> 30:32.831
♪

30:32.874 --> 30:34.006
- He's in.

30:34.049 --> 30:41.230
♪

30:42.405 --> 30:43.885
- You know,
you said that that guy

30:43.929 --> 30:45.756
would be fine if he told you
what you wanted to know.

30:45.800 --> 30:46.888
And then you threw him
out the window.

30:46.932 --> 30:47.889
-Do I have to remind you

30:47.933 --> 30:48.977
how many kids he killed?

30:49.021 --> 30:50.718
- That's not the point.

30:50.761 --> 30:52.285
I need to know
that I can trust you.

30:52.328 --> 30:54.330
- Jesus, Nadine,
this ain't the FBI.

30:54.374 --> 30:55.897
I'm here to take Atlas down.

30:55.941 --> 30:57.899
You really want to help me
hands can't stay clean.

30:57.943 --> 31:00.467
- My hands
spiked Hayes' scotch, remember?

31:00.510 --> 31:01.555
I'm not afraid
to do what it takes,

31:01.598 --> 31:03.426
but only when necessary.

31:03.470 --> 31:04.775
- I need to know
you have my back,

31:04.819 --> 31:06.386
no matter what.

31:06.429 --> 31:08.431
-You guys want
to shut the hell up?

31:08.475 --> 31:15.525
♪

31:26.449 --> 31:27.929
- Thank you.

31:27.973 --> 31:34.066
♪

31:34.109 --> 31:35.981
[clattering]

31:36.024 --> 31:39.071
- All right, let's go through
the safe contents

31:39.114 --> 31:41.421
one more time.

31:41.464 --> 31:42.857
- All right, I got a visual.

31:42.901 --> 31:44.728
- Head's up, Bob Lee.
Guard's coming your way,

31:44.772 --> 31:46.600
northeast corner.

31:46.643 --> 31:49.864
♪

31:49.908 --> 31:51.910
- I don't have eyes.

31:51.953 --> 31:53.520
- What?
What's going on?

31:53.563 --> 31:55.609
-I can't see shit,
I'm moving in.

31:55.652 --> 31:58.655
- That's not the plan, Isaac.

31:58.699 --> 32:00.440
Isaac?

32:00.483 --> 32:07.534
♪

32:09.840 --> 32:12.321
[thud]
- [gasps, gags]

32:14.106 --> 32:15.629
- It was all folders, files,

32:15.672 --> 32:17.457
uh, coded account numbers.

32:17.500 --> 32:18.980
His kill list, in progress,
which I don't even know

32:19.024 --> 32:21.591
why I was on because
his coffee was always hot

32:21.635 --> 32:24.116
and I told you,
I don't know anything.

32:24.159 --> 32:26.335
- You really should place
a higher value

32:26.379 --> 32:27.989
on yourself, Harris.

32:28.033 --> 32:30.600
- The more valuable you are,
the more vulnerable you are.

32:30.644 --> 32:32.733
- [chuckles]

32:32.776 --> 32:34.474
♪

32:34.517 --> 32:36.389
That might be
the first smart thing

32:36.432 --> 32:38.434
you've said
since you got here.

32:38.478 --> 32:40.480
- You're the one
who said I was bright.

32:40.523 --> 32:42.047
- I was lying.

32:42.090 --> 32:43.874
And so are you.

32:43.918 --> 32:45.572
Or maybe you're not.

32:45.615 --> 32:48.488
In either case,
consider that your last meal.

32:48.531 --> 32:51.099
Frank!
- Uh, okay, sir, I-I-I--

32:51.143 --> 32:53.667
- You know, it's funny
that you chose pancakes

32:53.710 --> 32:56.626
because that mathematician
that I mentioned, Hoffman,

32:56.670 --> 32:58.846
he had waffles.
We're done here.

32:58.889 --> 33:01.022
- J-just a second, right?

33:01.066 --> 33:02.502
T-there's got to be a way
that I can help, right?

33:02.545 --> 33:03.851
There's got to be.

33:03.894 --> 33:06.027
- Sorry, son,
I don't think you can.

33:06.071 --> 33:08.116
- Come on, move.
- Please.

33:08.160 --> 33:11.032
♪

33:11.076 --> 33:12.164
- They're moving him.

33:12.207 --> 33:16.777
♪

33:16.820 --> 33:19.693
Memphis, I need those guards
out front distracted.

33:19.736 --> 33:21.042
Can you draw their attention?

33:21.086 --> 33:22.130
- On it.

33:22.174 --> 33:25.438
♪

33:25.481 --> 33:27.527
[car door closes]

33:28.745 --> 33:30.573
[gun clicks]

33:30.617 --> 33:33.620
♪

33:33.663 --> 33:36.797
[car alarm blaring]

33:36.840 --> 33:43.891
♪

34:10.483 --> 34:13.486
[car alarm blaring]

34:13.529 --> 34:20.580
♪

34:22.582 --> 34:23.713
[door creaks open]

34:23.757 --> 34:26.629
[indistinct chatter]

34:26.673 --> 34:28.501
- Come on.

34:54.788 --> 35:01.838
♪

35:03.753 --> 35:05.059
- Guys, guys,
this is crazy, okay?

35:05.103 --> 35:06.626
I can't die down here,
seriously.

35:06.669 --> 35:08.062
W-w-what do you guys want?
Is it money?

35:08.106 --> 35:09.846
I can get you money.
That's not a problem.

35:09.890 --> 35:11.587
Whatever Red's paying you guys,
I can get you more.

35:11.631 --> 35:12.936
I--It's Frank, right?

35:12.980 --> 35:14.503
[blow landing]

35:14.547 --> 35:16.853
[gasping]

35:16.897 --> 35:17.985
- Come on, get up.

35:18.028 --> 35:23.904
♪

35:23.947 --> 35:25.079
[grunting]

35:25.123 --> 35:26.515
Groin!
Eyes!

35:26.559 --> 35:28.561
- [screams]
- Knees!

35:28.604 --> 35:34.132
♪

35:34.175 --> 35:35.959
- Go get him!
- Yes, sir.

35:36.003 --> 35:43.010
♪

36:07.643 --> 36:09.558
- Shit.

36:13.649 --> 36:14.998
The kid's got cavalry.

36:15.042 --> 36:16.739
Think they followed us
into the mine.

36:16.783 --> 36:19.002
- No shit.
[scoffs]

36:19.046 --> 36:21.701
God damn, Swagger.

36:21.744 --> 36:22.832
Where's your partner?

36:22.876 --> 36:24.834
- Still underground.

36:24.878 --> 36:26.923
- All right, get him up
and then blow it.

36:26.967 --> 36:28.273
I'm getting out of here.

36:28.316 --> 36:31.319
You'll have to find
your own way home.

36:31.363 --> 36:33.016
That's all.

36:33.060 --> 36:38.239
♪

36:41.329 --> 36:41.547
.

36:41.590 --> 36:44.332
[tense music]

36:44.898 --> 36:51.426
♪

36:57.737 --> 36:59.521
- Leave the kid
and get up here.

36:59.565 --> 37:01.088
We're gonna blow it.

37:01.131 --> 37:02.176
-Roger that.

37:02.220 --> 37:03.482
Setting the charge now.

37:03.525 --> 37:10.576
♪

37:14.710 --> 37:17.278
- Ah! Groin--
- Harris, Harris! It's me!

37:17.322 --> 37:18.758
It's me!
- Oh, thank Christ.

37:18.801 --> 37:20.194
They're coming.
- Shut up! Come on!

37:20.238 --> 37:21.413
We got to go!
- Okay.

37:21.456 --> 37:28.507
♪

37:50.224 --> 37:53.227
[both grunting]

37:53.271 --> 38:00.278
♪

38:12.290 --> 38:14.204
[panting]

38:14.248 --> 38:15.554
[distant explosions]

38:15.597 --> 38:17.207
- We're not gonna make it.

38:17.251 --> 38:19.645
- The exit's that way.
- Follow me!

38:19.688 --> 38:22.648
[rumbling]

38:22.691 --> 38:26.391
♪

38:26.434 --> 38:28.218
- Come on.

38:28.262 --> 38:32.701
♪

38:32.745 --> 38:34.355
Run, run!

38:53.679 --> 38:55.594
[metal creaks]

38:55.637 --> 38:59.859
♪

38:59.902 --> 39:02.862
[both coughing]

39:02.905 --> 39:10.130
♪

39:15.744 --> 39:17.659
- I still don't get it.

39:17.703 --> 39:20.183
why would he tell you
it was a decryption device?

39:20.227 --> 39:22.272
- Probably because
he was planning

39:22.316 --> 39:23.535
on murdering me.

39:23.578 --> 39:25.450
Where am I gonna sleep?

39:25.493 --> 39:27.321
- What I don't get
is why you can't be

39:27.365 --> 39:29.541
more specific
than a white keycard.

39:29.584 --> 39:31.107
- I was.

39:31.151 --> 39:32.457
I said it was thicker
than a keycard

39:32.500 --> 39:33.806
and more high-tech-looking.

39:33.849 --> 39:35.677
- He must have said
something else.

39:35.721 --> 39:38.288
- Only that it was called
the God Box,

39:38.332 --> 39:39.725
like I told you,
and that it was supposed to be

39:39.768 --> 39:42.728
in Hayes' safe,
but we all know it wasn't.

39:42.771 --> 39:44.643
- Or it was.

39:44.686 --> 39:45.731
There were four of us
in the room

39:45.774 --> 39:48.255
the day we emptied that safe.

39:48.298 --> 39:49.299
- Oh, let me see that.

39:49.343 --> 39:51.911
♪

39:51.954 --> 39:53.173
- If we don't have it.

39:53.216 --> 39:54.783
- Then Gregson does.

39:54.827 --> 39:58.221
♪

40:00.789 --> 40:02.791
- Hey.

40:02.835 --> 40:04.750
What happened to you?

40:04.793 --> 40:06.534
You smell like
a bonfire.

40:06.578 --> 40:08.275
- I almost was one.

40:08.318 --> 40:09.755
- What?

40:09.798 --> 40:12.497
- Can we just talk about it
in the morning?

40:12.540 --> 40:14.412
I'm beat.
[sighs]

40:16.283 --> 40:18.328
- Yeah.

40:28.556 --> 40:31.603
I went and saw Edie today.

40:31.646 --> 40:35.171
She gave me these
to give to you.

40:35.215 --> 40:36.303
You know,
there are a lot of ways

40:36.346 --> 40:38.610
that you're like your Dad.

40:38.653 --> 40:41.395
There's plenty of ways
that you're not.

40:46.531 --> 40:49.534
[solemn music]

40:49.577 --> 40:56.628
♪

41:44.980 --> 41:47.983
[dramatic music]

41:48.027 --> 41:55.251
♪
